1
00:00:02,502 --> 00:00:04,212
- [Chloe screams] <i>Aah!</i>
<i>- Chloe?!</i>

2
00:00:08,758 --> 00:00:10,427
<i>Did you see Edong?</i>

3
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:12,220
<i>Was he the one who did that?</i>

4
00:00:12,303 --> 00:00:14,389
[Erica] <i>He had the chance to hurt Chloe.</i>

5
00:00:14,472 --> 00:00:16,516
<i>But he didn't. What does he really want?!</i>

6
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:17,434
<i>Hello.</i>

7
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:18,852
<i>Hello.</i>

8
00:00:18,935 --> 00:00:19,728
<i>Seth!</i>

9
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:22,063
- [Althea groans]
- [Seth] <i>Let go! Ah!</i>

10
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:24,065
- [Althea grunts]
<i>- Althea, wake up!</i>

11
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:25,859
<i>Seth! Seth…</i>

12
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:28,695
- [Edong laughing]
<i>- Let me go!</i>

13
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,864
<i>Seth has nothing to do with this.</i>

14
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:33,450
<i>He's his mother's beloved son.</i>

15
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:35,910
<i>A mother's sin….</i>

16
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:38,204
<i>is also her child's.</i>

17
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:40,081
<i>Seth!</i>

18
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,338
Seth…

19
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:51,468
- [breath quivering]
- [tense music playing]

20
00:00:55,346 --> 00:00:57,807
- [man] What happened here?
- Excuse me. Excuse me.

21
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,602
Baby… Seth?

22
00:01:01,019 --> 00:01:01,895
Seth!

23
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:03,646
[Alice sobbing] Hey.

24
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:05,940
- [Scott] Are you okay?
- [Alice] baby?

25
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:09,569
I thought I lost you. [sniffles, sobs]

26
00:01:09,652 --> 00:01:11,821
[Scott] You're alive. You're alive.

27
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:12,864
[Alice] You're okay, baby.

28
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:15,950
[sobbing]

29
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:18,953
- You're okay. You're okay.
- [Alice sniffling]

30
00:01:19,037 --> 00:01:24,626
[poignant music playing]

31
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:37,639
[theme music playing]

32
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:49,127
[Edward] I was about to grab Seth.

33
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:50,545
[sighs loudly]

34
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,173
But…

35
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,010
He suddenly pulled out a knife.

36
00:02:58,177 --> 00:03:02,432
- [grunting]
- [knife slashing]

37
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:06,936
- [Edong laughing]
- [dogs barking]

38
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,146
- [skin rips]
- [Edong grunts]

39
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:10,023
[dogs continue barking]

40
00:03:10,106 --> 00:03:11,274
<i>- Hey! What are you doing?!</i>
<i>- What's going on?!</i>

41
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:12,358
- [Edong grunts]
- [thud]

42
00:03:12,442 --> 00:03:16,404
[dogs continue barking]

43
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:17,405
- [Edward groans]
<i>- Hey.</i>

44
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:20,450
[Locsin] That looks deep.

45
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,744
Your hand really took a hit.

46
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:25,580
[sighs sharply]

47
00:03:25,663 --> 00:03:28,958
I don't know how I managed to face him.

48
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:32,003
All that was on my mind was…

49
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:35,673
getting Seth back.

50
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:40,428
[pensive music playing]

51
00:03:40,511 --> 00:03:41,804
[sighs]

52
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:45,350
What did the doctor say?

53
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:48,937
[sighs, sniffles]

54
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,481
Everything seems normal.

55
00:03:52,106 --> 00:03:54,984
They didn't find
anything wrong with his CT scan.

56
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:57,153
But he does have minor injuries.

57
00:03:57,737 --> 00:04:00,573
And there's still
the possibility of a concussion.

58
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:01,950
[sighs sharply]

59
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,201
But…

60
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:05,703
They have to observe him for a few hours

61
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:08,581
to make sure he didn't
sustain any other injuries.

62
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:13,503
We almost lost him!

63
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:20,802
[sniffling, sobbing]

64
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:27,475
- [pensive music continues]
- [Alice continues sobbing]

65
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,785
[Erica pants] <i>Althea!</i>

66
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,169
<i>Althea. Althea!</i>

67
00:04:55,712 --> 00:04:56,838
<i>Althea.</i>

68
00:04:56,921 --> 00:05:01,968
[pensive music continues]

69
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:04,971
[Althea] <i>Erica!</i>

70
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:08,474
[Erica] <i>You don't</i>
<i>have to message me anymore.</i>

71
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:10,184
<i>We no longer have a connection.</i>

72
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:12,937
<i>Whatever your mother and I had before…</i>

73
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:14,397
<i>it's long over.</i>

74
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,316
<i>I don't have anything</i>
<i>to do with your family anymore.</i>

75
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:21,446
[pensive music continues]

76
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,918
[music fades]

77
00:05:36,627 --> 00:05:37,837
[Althea] Erica?

78
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:42,467
Ah…

79
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,760
[Althea winces]

80
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:45,928
How do you feel?

81
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,015
M-My head hurts.

82
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:50,892
- [inhales shakily]
- [sighs]

83
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:53,519
Erica, where's Seth?

84
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:55,897
And Auntie Christina?

85
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:57,607
- She--
- They're fine.

86
00:05:58,232 --> 00:05:59,984
Seth sustained minor injuries,

87
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,487
but doctors are already looking after him.

88
00:06:03,112 --> 00:06:05,656
Auntie Christina's with Rose.

89
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:09,410
Worry about yourself first.

90
00:06:10,078 --> 00:06:11,079
Where's Mama?

91
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:13,081
And Papa? I haven't--

92
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:14,290
I've already let them know.

93
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:20,963
You shouldn't have faced him alone.

94
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:23,091
You should have called Uncle Edward

95
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:24,675
or asked for help.

96
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,594
He had Seth, Erica.

97
00:06:26,677 --> 00:06:29,097
- I didn't think--
- He's a murderer!

98
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:32,016
You should be grateful that's all you got!

99
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:39,941
- [huffs]
- [somber music playing]

100
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:41,192
- You sound like a big sister.
- [Erica sniffles]

101
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:44,987
Uncle Edward said…

102
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,865
you were like that even in high school.

103
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:50,368
You don't speak much, but…

104
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:51,911
whenever there's a problem,

105
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:55,164
you're one of the first ones to help.

106
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,749
You don't care if you get hurt.

107
00:06:58,584 --> 00:07:01,671
You defended Louisa from Kyle.

108
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:05,424
And on the day Louisa died…

109
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:08,553
Alice told Uncle Edward that…

110
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:12,098
you even chased
the killer and tried to stop him.

111
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:18,479
Erica, Alice said…

112
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:22,233
that we have the same smile.

113
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,697
Looks like that's not
the only thing we have in common.

114
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:32,869
[somber music continues]

115
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:34,036
[Annette] Althea!

116
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:36,038
Althea!

117
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:40,001
Dear! What happened?!

118
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:42,253
[Frank] Dear…

119
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:44,464
[Annette] What did he do? Did he hurt you?

120
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:50,428
Edong Santiago attacked
them at Uncle Edward's house.

121
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:54,432
[gasps]

122
00:07:57,852 --> 00:07:59,270
I'll call the doctor.

123
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:02,398
Erica.

124
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,692
[music fades]

125
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:06,068
[Alice] <i>You have to leave.</i>

126
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,410
You and Seth.

127
00:08:14,994 --> 00:08:16,954
You have to go back to the US.

128
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:20,333
We can't give that monster
another chance at our son.

129
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:21,834
We need to make sure he's safe.

130
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:23,753
You're coming with us.

131
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:26,714
I… I can't!

132
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,095
Alice, this man…

133
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:34,597
He's dangerous.

134
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:37,016
He'd hurt a child without blinking.

135
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:38,643
Of course you're coming with us.

136
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:46,984
You know, when I was
frantically looking for Seth…

137
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,946
I suddenly remembered something.

138
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:54,617
Remember the day I disappeared
at the market with my mom?

139
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,786
I saw someone.

140
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,288
I was lured away.

141
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:01,207
[melancholic music playing]

142
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,876
Maybe the same way Edong lured our son.

143
00:09:05,169 --> 00:09:06,587
I don't know what I was lured with.

144
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:08,381
Maybe… a toy.

145
00:09:08,464 --> 00:09:09,382
I don't know.

146
00:09:10,883 --> 00:09:13,594
But, Scott,
I- I finally remembered something.

147
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,638
I finally remembered something.

148
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:19,058
I'm so close to getting
the answers I finally need.

149
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:21,769
I can't leave.

150
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,855
You really think I'll just leave you here?

151
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:26,899
With that lunatic still out there?

152
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:29,694
I'm scared, too.

153
00:09:32,446 --> 00:09:34,156
But if I keep running away,

154
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,159
this won't end.

155
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:39,620
I have to stay.

156
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:43,541
I have to end this. Now.

157
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:48,296
[music becomes uneasy]

158
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:03,603
[uneasy music continues]

159
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,357
- Did he kill someone again?
- [music fades]

160
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:13,029
No.

161
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:18,159
One of Alice's bodyguards got hurt, but…

162
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:19,785
he's okay now.

163
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,833
Lucas, what's wrong?

164
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,634
Yuri is dead.

165
00:10:35,384 --> 00:10:39,680
[ominous music playing]

166
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:40,931
I'm sorry.

167
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,727
[chuckles bitterly]

168
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:54,320
[sobbing]

169
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:02,119
We can find and stop him.

170
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:07,458
[ominous music continues]

171
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:22,056
- [music fades]
- [crickets chirping]

172
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:25,726
[breathes heavily]

173
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:36,195
Chloe's room is all cleaned up.

174
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:40,366
But I don't think she'd be
able to sleep there for now.

175
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:44,286
She can sleep in our room.

176
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:47,415
I'll just sleep in the living room.

177
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:54,422
[somber music playing]

178
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:58,175
[sobbing]

179
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:09,770
Beth.

180
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:17,945
[sobbing continues]

181
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:25,995
[music fades]

182
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:26,996
[phone chimes]

183
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:30,875
[crickets chirping]

184
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:34,086
"GIRL, EDONG'S STILL ALIVE!
WE SHOULD ALL BE CAREFUL!"

185
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,337
Edong Santiago?

186
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:38,132
- Yeah, dude. Arnie and the others saw him.
- [tense music swells]

187
00:12:38,215 --> 00:12:41,552
Good thing they arrived. Otherwise,
the boy and the old man would've died.

188
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:43,179
- [gasps]
- [music ends]

189
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:48,642
[breathing heavily]

190
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:56,567
[tender music playing]

191
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:57,693
[Scott] He's fine.

192
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:00,779
They said to watch out for vomiting

193
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:02,406
or any signs of confusion.

194
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,867
And so far, there's nothing.

195
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,130
[Mel] Alice?

196
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:19,798
[music fades]

197
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:25,012
- [Alice] Hey.
- [Mel] Hey.

198
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,097
Oh.

199
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,267
How are you? How's Seth?

200
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:32,061
[sighs]

201
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:34,563
Why did you come here?

202
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:37,191
You've got a lot on your plate.
You didn't have to.

203
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:38,901
Of course I have to.

204
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:40,945
I was so worried.

205
00:13:41,028 --> 00:13:45,074
[uneasy music playing]

206
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:51,997
[knocking on door]

207
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:55,834
Oh, Beth.

208
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:57,002
Come in.

209
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:03,008
I know I've said a lot of things.

210
00:14:04,134 --> 00:14:05,302
Too many things.

211
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:09,390
But, Alice, you're right.

212
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:11,559
This isn't just about me.

213
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:15,521
[Beth] <i>You're right.</i>

214
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:17,523
[sobs]

215
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:19,275
<i>I'm so selfish.</i>

216
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:22,945
[uneasy music continues]

217
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:26,490
<i>We almost lost our daughter because of me.</i>

218
00:14:31,328 --> 00:14:33,706
<i>I'm so selfish.</i>

219
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:37,626
I need to protect my family now.

220
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:40,921
I'm not going to let
Edong come near them again.

221
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,009
I know now.

222
00:14:45,509 --> 00:14:47,177
We need to work together.

223
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:49,054
I need to help.

224
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:53,809
[uneasy music continues]

225
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:56,812
It doesn't matter what I believe.

226
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,983
All of our lives are in danger,

227
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,527
including the people we love.

228
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:06,280
We need to stop Edong now.

229
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:09,366
Since there's another witness,

230
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,535
the police now
believes that Edong is still alive.

231
00:15:11,952 --> 00:15:14,163
Marco and I have been talking to them,

232
00:15:14,246 --> 00:15:15,456
not just about the manhunt,

233
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:17,750
but also about
a protection detail for all of us.

234
00:15:19,043 --> 00:15:22,129
We need to alert
our families and close friends.

235
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,632
Because Edong is here in Amurao.

236
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:26,425
And he's not going to leave

237
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:29,011
because everyone
he wants to take revenge on is here.

238
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:32,681
[uneasy music continues]

239
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:42,775
[music fades]

240
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:45,611
[birds chirp distantly]

241
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:03,253
[foreboding music playing]

242
00:16:21,271 --> 00:16:26,777
[foreboding music continues]

243
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:50,175
[foreboding music continues]

244
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:11,530
[unsettling music continues]

245
00:17:16,076 --> 00:17:17,953
<i>Seth has nothing to do with this.</i>

246
00:17:18,746 --> 00:17:19,913
<i>He's just a child.</i>

247
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:21,832
<i>He's innocent.</i>

248
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:28,464
[foreboding music continues]

249
00:17:30,507 --> 00:17:33,594
<i>He's his mother's beloved son.</i>

250
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:36,513
[music becomes sinister]

251
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,807
<i>His mother's sin…</i>

252
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,396
<i>is also his sin.</i>

253
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:48,734
[sinister music continues]

254
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,404
<i>I won't let you take him.</i>

255
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,409
[laughing]

256
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:04,833
[laughing continues]

257
00:18:10,672 --> 00:18:13,467
[inhales sarcastically]

258
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:25,604
- [heart beating loudly]
- [sinister music continues]

259
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:32,569
- [knife slashing]
- [groans]

260
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:35,572
[both grunting]

261
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:36,949
[laughs]

262
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:46,250
- [knife slashing]
- [both grunting]

263
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:48,001
[panting]

264
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:53,590
[sinister music continues]

265
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:57,261
[Edong grunts]

266
00:18:58,053 --> 00:19:02,224
[breathing heavily]

267
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:07,479
[tense music stings]

268
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,275
- Hey!
- [Edward grunts]

269
00:19:12,359 --> 00:19:13,277
- [blow lands]
- [grunts]

270
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:15,779
[sinister music continues]

271
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:27,624
[sinister music intensifies]

272
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,173
[music fades]

273
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:35,674
What are you?

274
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:41,013
[unsettling music playing]

275
00:19:54,985 --> 00:20:00,115
[unsettling music continues]

276
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:25,474
[unsettling music intensifies]

277
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:43,575
[unsettling music crescendos]

278
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,411
[Beth]<i> I'll help find Edong.</i>

279
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:47,996
[Alice] <i>What about</i>
<i>admitting to what we did?</i>

280
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:51,250
<i>Chloe's smart. If you</i>
<i>explain it to her, she will understand.</i>

281
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,377
<i>You'll never understand</i>
<i>because you don't have any kids!</i>

282
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:54,962
<i>You don't even have anyone in your life!</i>

283
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:57,047
<i>- Beth.</i>
- [Marco] <i>I've talked to the police.</i>

284
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:59,091
<i>They’ll search all</i>
<i>the places where Edong could be hiding.</i>

285
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:00,801
<i>Why did you even save me</i>

286
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:03,595
<i>if you would just stop my mission?</i>

287
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:05,097
<i>Why?!</i>

288
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:06,306
<i>Why me?!</i>

289
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,809
[laughing]<i> Is this another test?</i>

290
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:12,145
<i>Why do you keep testing me?!</i>
